Ghana Chamber of Mines CEO Joyce Aryee Resigns After 10 Years

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-09-30T13:01:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/ghana-chamber-of-mines-ceo-joyce-aryee-resigns-after-10-years.html
The  Ghana Chamber of Mines  said
Chief Executive Officer Joyce Aryee resigned after 10 years in
the post.  Her replacement will be announced soon, said the Accra-
based group, which represents mining companies including
 AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  and Newmont Ghana Gold Ltd., in an e-
mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  